At all events it seems certain that since Dr. MacEgan’s translation to Meath, Clonmacnoise never was an Indepenclent See. Here it seems fitting to investigate the question as to what ecclesiastical Province Clonmacnoise formerly belonged; sor just as Meath and Ardagh administered her at different times, so Tuam and Armagh held her alternately in subjection as a Suffragan Diocese.
